  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 12 factors meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Test samples — carries a required level of 3 but achieved level of 2, reflecting a shortfall in the number of independent experimental replicates available at the target operating conditions. The decision record accepts the package on the basis of extensive prior validation heritage, expert panel consensus, and Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds that nominally encompass the clinical threshold, but these justifications do not formally close the one-step level gap.",
